---
title: One-Pot Mexican Quinoa with Sweet Corn, Feta, and Jalapeño
description: Say goodbye to huge piles of dishes and long after-dinner cleanups. We’ve created a one-pot Mexican wonder loaded with hearty quinoa, black beans, and diced tomatoes—not to mention chunks upon chunks of creamy feta cheese.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pot-mexican-quinoa-6c184009.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pot-mexican-quinoa-356bdbb2.pdf
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 613 kcal
  fat: 20 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 550 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-mexican-quinoa-577d5ee213e9d663788b4569
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Mince the @garlic{2%cloves}. Shuck the @corn on the cob{1}, then cut the kernels off the cob. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Finely chop the @jalapeño{1}(finely chopped), removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%box}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the garlic, scallion whites, and as much jalapeño as you like (start with a little and go from there). Cook ~{1%minute}, until fragrant. Add the @chili powder{1%tsp} and @cumin{1%tsp}. Cook another ~{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @quinoa{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, beans, corn, @diced tomatoes{1%box}, and @water{1%cup} to the pan. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce heat to low. Cook about ~{15%minutes}, until quinoa is cooked through.

Once tender, fluff the quinoa mixture with a #fork{}. Season with salt and pepper. Serve with the scallion greens and @feta cheese{1/4%cup} on top. Enjoy!